  body
    .container
      h1.text-center FCC API Basejump: Timestamp Microservice
      .jumbotron
        h3 User Stories:
        blockquote
          ul
            | 1) I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: 15th October, 2017).
          ul
            | 2) If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
          ul
            | 3) If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
        h3 Example Usage
        code https://timestamp-hemakshis.herokuapp.com/api/15th%20October,%202017
        br
        code https://timestamp-hemakshis.herokuapp.com/api/1508025600
        h3 Example Output
        code {"unix": "1508025600", "natural": "15th October, 2017"}
